[SN]TITLE[SN]
Holyrood's presiding officer asks MSPs to stop chuntering

[SN]FIRST-SENTENCE[SN]
Holyrood's Presiding Officer Ken Macintosh halts First Minister's Questions to ask MSP to stop the interrupting.

[SN]RESTBODY[SN]
23 February 2017 Last updated at 16:30 GMT
He said: "I am not expecting reverential silence, but just as there shouldn't be chuntering as the first minister is trying to answer questions, similarly there shouldn't be interventions when someone is asking a question."
